UNITED AIRLINES WINE CELLAR
Under the direction of author and veteran wine judge Bob Thompson, United Airlines Cellar Committee
each year conducts a rigorously controlled blind tasting to choose six superior American wines
from a field of more than 100. Of these, you will be offered one of our Cellar's
white and red wines on today's flight.
RED WINE
CABERNET SAUVIGNON
Buena Vista Sonoma-Carneros 1983, Reserve
From one of California's coolest vineyard districts,
the Buena Vista Reserve is tart, lively, refreshing.
Fetzer Lake County 1984
Upland vineyards in Lake County yield a light,
markedly fruity Cabernet ideal for early use.
J. Pedroncelli Sonoma 1983
The Pedroncelli shows fully developed Cabernet flavors
plus welcome overtones from long ageing in barrel.
WHITE WINE
CHARDONNAY
Corbett Canyon Central Coast 1984, Coastal Classic
Coastal Classic typified its grape's flavor in the Central Coast -
San Luis Obispo and Santa Barbara counties.
Glen Ellen California 1985, Proprietor's Reserve
So gentle and polished is this Chardonnay that it tastes
almost as pleasant alone as in the company of food.
SAUVIGNON BLANC
Beaulieu Vineyard Napa Valley 1985
Sauvignon Blanc can be overwhelmingly flavorful,
but Beaulieu tames the variety to perfection.
SPARKLING WINES
Hanns Kornell California Brut
True to its name, Hanns Kornell is patterned after traditional German sparkling wine.
